{"config":{"separator":"[\\s\\-_,:!=\\[\\]()\\\\\"`/]+|\\.(?!\\d)"},"items":[{"location":"","level":1,"title":"DAMNIT - API","text":"","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#damnit-api","level":1,"title":"DAMNIT - API","text":"<p><code>damnit_api</code> is a Python package that handles the integration of the Damnit database and web frontend. This utilizes FastAPI for the web framework, Strawberry for the GraphQL API, and SQLAlchemy for the database management.</p>","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#setup","level":2,"title":"Setup","text":"<p>Get the environment variables for authentication from TeamPass, and put them in a <code>.env</code> file in this directory.</p> <p><code>uv</code> is used for project management, install it if required, see the uv docs for more information.</p> <p>This project has some <code>pre-commit</code> hooks set up, after installing and activating the running <code>pre-commit install</code> will install the hooks and their dependencies.</p> <p>To start the API server run:</p> <pre><code># Start by calling uvicorn, allows for passing uvicorn flags directly:\nuv run uvicorn damnit_api.main:create_app\n\n# Start server by calling the `main` function directly, this only allows\n# configuration via env vars or by modifying the `.env` value, has slightly\n# improved logging:\nuv run -m damnit_api.main\n</code></pre> <p>If port <code>8000</code> is not free you can change the port number, by using the <code>--port NNNN</code> flag on the <code>uvicorn</code> command, or by setting the <code>DW_API_UVICORN__PORT</code> env var if running <code>damnit_api.main</code>.</p> <p>An interactive GraphQL interface can be accessed at <code>localhost:8000/graphql</code>. More information can be found on the GraphiQL readme.</p> <p>Running the server in a container can be done by:</p> <pre><code># Running container directly (from the repo root):\npodman build -t damnit-web-api -f api/Dockerfile .\npodman run --env-file api/.env --rm -it damnit-web-api\n\n# Via compose (from api/):\npodman compose up\n</code></pre>","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#usage","level":2,"title":"Usage","text":"","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#1-query-the-metadata","level":3,"title":"1. Query the metadata","text":"<pre><code>query TableMetadataQuery {\n  metadata(database: {proposal: \"&lt;PROPOSAL_NUMBER&gt;\"})\n}\n</code></pre> <p>This returns a JSON snapshot for the proposal:</p> <ul> <li><code>runs</code> - sorted list of run numbers in the proposal</li> <li><code>variables</code> - map of variable name to its title and tags (includes the   known variables listed below alongside any user-defined ones)</li> <li><code>tags</code> - map of tag name to its id and the variables it groups</li> <li><code>timestamp</code> - last update time, in milliseconds since the Unix epoch</li> </ul>","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#2-query-the-runs","level":3,"title":"2. Query the runs","text":"<p>For instance, to fetch the first 10 runs of proposal <code>2956</code> along with all of their variables:</p> <pre><code>query TableDataQuery($per_page: Int = 10) {\n  runs(database: {proposal: \"2956\"}, per_page: $per_page) {\n    variables {\n      name\n      value\n      dtype\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>Each run is returned as a flat list of <code>DamnitVariable</code> entries (<code>name</code>, <code>value</code>, <code>dtype</code>). One can pass a list of <code>names</code> to select variables:</p> <pre><code>query TableDataQuery($per_page: Int = 10) {\n  runs(database: {proposal: \"2956\"}, per_page: $per_page) {\n    variables(names: [\"proposal\", \"run\"]) {\n      name\n      value\n      dtype\n    }\n  }\n}\n</code></pre> <p>The following variables are always present, in addition to any user-defined ones from the proposal's context file:</p> <ul> <li><code>proposal</code></li> <li><code>run</code></li> <li><code>start_time</code></li> <li><code>added_at</code></li> </ul> <p>Pagination is controlled with <code>page</code> (1-indexed, defaults to <code>1</code>) and <code>per_page</code> (defaults to <code>10</code>).</p>","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#3-subscribe-to-latest-data","level":3,"title":"3. Subscribe to latest data","text":"<pre><code>subscription LatestDataSubscription {\n  latest_data(database: {proposal: \"&lt;PROPOSAL_NUMBER&gt;\"}, timestamp: &lt;TIMESTAMP&gt;)\n}\n</code></pre> <p>This returns the following:</p> <ul> <li>list of (new) runs</li> <li>updated metadata</li> </ul> <p>Note that the <code>timestamp</code> is in milliseconds since Unix epoch.</p>","path":["DAMNIT - API"],"tags":[]},{"location":"deployment/","level":1,"title":"Deployment","text":"<p>Production runs on <code>max-exfl457</code> under the <code>xdamnprd</code> account, served by Podman Compose from <code>~/srv/damnit-web/damnit-web-prod/api</code>. The <code>compose.prod.yml</code> file builds the image from source and serves the API over HTTPS on port 8443.</p>","path":["Deployment"],"tags":[]},{"location":"deployment/#deploy-a-new-version","level":2,"title":"Deploy a new version","text":"<p>SSH to the host, pull the latest code, and rebuild:</p> <pre><code>ssh xdamnprd@max-exfl457.desy.de\ncd ~/srv/damnit-web/damnit-web-prod/api\ngit pull\npodman compose -f compose.prod.yml up -d --build\n</code></pre> <p><code>--build</code> rebuilds the image from the pulled code. Without it, the container keeps running the old image.</p>","path":["Deployment"],"tags":[]},{"location":"deployment/#quick-restart","level":2,"title":"Quick restart","text":"<p>To restart the running service without pulling or rebuilding:</p> <pre><code>damnit-web-up\n</code></pre>","path":["Deployment"],"tags":[]},{"location":"deployment/#housekeeping","level":2,"title":"Housekeeping","text":"<p>Past rebuilds leave old, untagged images behind. Clean them up every now and then:</p> <pre><code>podman image prune -f\n</code></pre> <p>To rebuild from scratch and ignore the layer cache:</p> <pre><code>podman compose -f compose.prod.yml build --no-cache\npodman compose -f compose.prod.yml up -d\n</code></pre>","path":["Deployment"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/architecture/","level":1,"title":"Architecture","text":"<p>Todo</p>","path":["Development","Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/ci-cd/","level":1,"title":"CI/CD","text":"<p>GitHub Actions run the API's checks and publish its documentation. The workflows live in <code>.github/workflows/</code>.</p>","path":["Development","CI/CD"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/ci-cd/#testing","level":2,"title":"Testing","text":"<p><code>test-api.yml</code> runs on pull requests and pushes to <code>main</code> that change files under <code>api/</code>, <code>pyproject.toml</code>, or <code>uv.lock</code>.</p> <p>It runs three checks with <code>uv</code> on Python 3.13:</p> <ul> <li>Lint: <code>ruff check</code></li> <li>Format: <code>ruff format --check</code></li> <li>Tests: <code>pytest</code></li> </ul>","path":["Development","CI/CD"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/ci-cd/#documentation","level":2,"title":"Documentation","text":"<p><code>deploy-docs.yml</code> builds this site and publishes it to GitHub Pages.</p> <ul> <li>Build: <code>zensical build</code> renders the site from the Markdown pages and   from source docstrings.</li> <li>Publish: the output is pushed to the <code>docs/api/</code> folder on the   <code>gh-pages</code> branch, served at   https://european-xfel.github.io/DAMNIT-web/docs/api/.</li> </ul> <p>It runs on pushes to <code>main</code> that change the docs, the API source, or the build dependencies (<code>api/pyproject.toml</code>, <code>uv.lock</code>), and can also be run by hand from the Actions tab. Because the reference is built from docstrings, a change under <code>api/src/**</code> rebuilds the docs too.</p>","path":["Development","CI/CD"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/docs/","level":1,"title":"Documentation","text":"<p>Documentation is generated using Zensical.</p> <ul> <li>mkdocstrings (with the Python handler) renders API documentation from source-code docstrings.</li> </ul>","path":["Development","Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/docs/#tips","level":2,"title":"Tips","text":"<p>Write documentation as close to the code as possible. Only a few overarching/'meta' topics (this, setup, architecture, deployment, etc...) need to be written into the <code>./docs</code> directory directly.</p> <p>Aim to:</p> <ul> <li>Use module-level docstrings.</li> <li>Use cross-references where applicable, e.g. <code>damnit_api.main.create_app</code>.</li> <li> <p>Pull docstrings into a page with an inline <code>mkdocstrings</code> block, e.g.:</p> <pre><code>::: damnit_api.main\n    options:\n      heading_level: 2\n</code></pre> </li> </ul>","path":["Development","Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/docs/#setup","level":2,"title":"Setup","text":"<p>Build or serve the site (all commands use the <code>docs</code> dependency group):</p> <pre><code>uv run --group docs zensical build  # build the static site into ./site\nuv run --group docs zensical serve  # live-reloading preview on :8000\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/","level":1,"title":"Notes","text":"Generate script <pre><code>#!/bin/env sh\n\n# Fetch latest spec\npnpm --package=@redocly/cli dlx -- redocly \\\n    bundle \\\n    https://in.xfel.eu/metadata/api-docs/v1/swagger.yaml \\\n    -o openapi.yaml\n\n# Create slimmed down version with only relevant schemas\npnpm --package=@redocly/cli dlx -- redocly \\\n    bundle \\\n    wrapper.yaml \\\n    -o openapi.slim.yaml \\\n    --dereferenced\n\n# Generate models\ndatamodel-codegen \\\n    --input openapi.slim.yaml \\\n    --input-file-type openapi \\\n    --output-model-type pydantic_v2.BaseModel \\\n    --formatters ruff-format \\\n    --use-annotated \\\n    --use-union-operator \\\n    --use-standard-collections \\\n    --reuse-model \\\n    --target-python-version 3.13 \\\n    --output models.py\n\n# Second pass to format with ruff\nuv run ruff format models.py\nuv run ruff check --fix models.py\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor","level":2,"title":"Vendored MyMdC Model Generation","text":"<p>Models generated from the OpenAPI specification for MyMDC.</p> <p>This is done by:</p> <ol> <li>Fetching the OpenAPI spec from MyMDC using <code>redocly</code>.</li> <li>Filtering the spec to only include models we're interested in by using a wrapper spec   and <code>redocly bundle</code>.</li> <li>Generating pydantic models using <code>datamodel-codegen</code>.</li> </ol> <p>Running <code>generate.sh</code> will regenerate these models.</p> <p>To add new models, update the wrapper spec in <code>wrapper.yaml</code> by adding in additional schemas.</p> <p>Warning</p> <p>Some corrections are applied to the generated models in [<code>damnit_api._mymdc.vendor</code>]</p>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.__all__","level":3,"title":"__all__  <small><code>module-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>__all__ = ['GetProposals', 'InstrumentCycles', 'Users', 'UsersProposal', 'UsersProposals']\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals","level":3,"title":"GetProposals","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>GetProposals</code></p>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.abstract","level":4,"title":"abstract  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>abstract: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.beamtime_end_at","level":4,"title":"beamtime_end_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>beamtime_end_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.beamtime_start_at","level":4,"title":"beamtime_start_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>beamtime_start_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.beamtimes","level":4,"title":"beamtimes  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>beamtimes: list[Beamtime] | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.begin_at","level":4,"title":"begin_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>begin_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.data_archived_at","level":4,"title":"data_archived_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>data_archived_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.def_proposal_path","level":4,"title":"def_proposal_path  <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>def_proposal_path: str\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.description","level":4,"title":"description  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>description: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.end_at","level":4,"title":"end_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>end_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.expected_data_archive_at","level":4,"title":"expected_data_archive_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>expected_data_archive_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.experiment_data_contact_id","level":4,"title":"experiment_data_contact_id  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>experiment_data_contact_id: int | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_auto_run_quality","level":4,"title":"flg_auto_run_quality  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_auto_run_quality: int | None = -1\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_available","level":4,"title":"flg_available  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_available: bool | None = True\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_beamtime_status","level":4,"title":"flg_beamtime_status  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_beamtime_status: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_cloneable_status","level":4,"title":"flg_cloneable_status  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_cloneable_status: str | None = 'NC'\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_data_archived_notification","level":4,"title":"flg_data_archived_notification  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_data_archived_notification: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_preferred_data_output","level":4,"title":"flg_preferred_data_output  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_preferred_data_output: str | None = 'R'\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_proposal_system","level":4,"title":"flg_proposal_system  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_proposal_system: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.flg_public","level":4,"title":"flg_public  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>flg_public: bool | None = False\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.id","level":4,"title":"id  <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>id: int\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.GetProposals.instrument_cycle_id","level":4,"title":"instrument_cycle_id  <small><code>instance-