ed_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>updated_at: str | None = ''\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.Users.upex_synced_at","level":4,"title":"upex_synced_at  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>upex_synced_at: str | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.UsersProposal","level":3,"title":"UsersProposal","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>BaseModel</code></p>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.UsersProposal.proposal_id","level":4,"title":"proposal_id  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>proposal_id: int | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.UsersProposal.proposal_number","level":4,"title":"proposal_number  <small><code>class-attribute</code></small> <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>proposal_number: int | None = None\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.UsersProposals","level":3,"title":"UsersProposals","text":"<p>               Bases: <code>RootModel[list[UsersProposal]]</code></p>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/notes/#damnit_api._mymdc.vendor.UsersProposals.root","level":4,"title":"root  <small><code>instance-attribute</code></small>","text":"<pre><code>root: list[UsersProposal]\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Notes"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/security/","level":1,"title":"Security","text":"<p>Authentication is handled by an external OAuth client, with authorization handled by queries made to MyMdC using the authenticated users information.</p>","path":["Development","Security"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/security/#description","level":2,"title":"Description","text":"<p>The API server uses a secure/private OAuth2 client to redirect users to the OAuth2 provider's login page. After the user logs in and is redirected back, their</p> <p>Users log in via the 3rd party OAuth provider (in our case EuXFEL's Keycloak realm), following the standard OAuth 2 flow.</p> <p>On redirect, their token is stored in a session cookie, which is available to the API code via the Starlette Session Middleware.</p> <p>The user information stored in this token contains the users username in a field <code>preferred_username</code> (e.g. <code>roscar</code>).</p> <p>This username is used to query MyMdC's user information endpoints to find out what proposals the user has access to.</p> <p>Function calls/dependencies are set up such that any endpoint which requires access to data that needs authorization checks will always call a function (<code>get_proposal_meta</code>) that verifies the user is allowed to view that resource.</p>","path":["Development","Security"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/setup/","level":1,"title":"Setup","text":"","path":["Development","Setup"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/setup/#installation","level":2,"title":"Installation","text":"<p>Todo</p>","path":["Development","Setup"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/setup/#debugging","level":2,"title":"Debugging","text":"<p>If using <code>VSCode</code>, the following <code>launch.json</code> file can be used to start the server with the built-in debugger:</p> <pre><code>{\n    \"version\": \"0.2.0\",\n    \"configurations\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"Python Debugger: Module\",\n            \"type\": \"debugpy\",\n            \"request\": \"launch\",\n            \"module\": \"damnit_api.main\"\n        }\n    ]\n}\n</code></pre>","path":["Development","Setup"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/setup/#configuration","level":2,"title":"Configuration","text":"","path":["Development","Setup"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/setup/#mocked-data","level":3,"title":"Mocked Data","text":"<p>Mocked data sources are implemented in some of the modules.</p>","path":["Development","Setup"],"tags":[]},{"location":"dev/setup/#metadata-mymdc-and-damnit-data-paths","level":4,"title":"Metadata - MyMdC and DAMNIT Data Paths","text":"<p>If the configuration for MyMdC's API is not provided then a mock API response file will be used. By default this is the file in <code>./tests/mock/_mymdc.json</code>, feel free to update this as required or change it in place.</p> <p>Alternatively, <code>mock_responses_file</code> can be provided with a path to a different file (e.g. via <code>DW_API_MYMDC__MOCK_RESPONSES_FILE</code>).</p> <p>Important</p> <p>For convenience, this file sets <code>def_proposal_path</code> for proposal <code>900000</code> to <code>/tmp/gpfs/exfel/exp/HSLAB/201730/p900000/raw\"</code>. As this field is what is used to find the proposal directory that means you can place damnit data in <code>/tmp/gpfs/exfel/exp/HSLAB/201730/p900000/usr/Shared/amore</code> and API calls will read the contents of that directory.</p>","path":["Development","Setup"],"tags":[]}]}